			<div class="message">I would be against rebar,  personally. I remember it coming up in a water treatment seminar having lead in its alloy. I'll see if i can find the documentation.</div>
			
		<hr />
	</div>
</div>Rebar is either pure stainless steel, or &quot;junk&quot; metals in iron.  Any lead would be trace amounts in the iron.  And that kind of lead isn't going to get picked up by the plants.  It's dangerous in water, because a person might literally drink those lead particles.</blockquote>
	</div>
</li><li class="postbit blockbody" id="post_19">
